          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " you can see exactly what era this vehicle came from and it makes no effort to try and be more modern or stylish than some of its counterparts. Another car might have tried and failed to predict future trends in the automotive industry, such as the C4 Corvette which had  an odd digital display dash that didn't really fit with the overall vehicle itself. Rather this  automobile was made in 1977, a fact the engineers are obviously quite proud of and wanted to showcase. For some this might be a negative as older cars are typically more worn out because of being driven for so long. However you would be hard-pressed to find many, if any, imperfections on the body or interior of this incredible American hatchback.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
